usage: rebar_reconciler [-h] [--repo-root REPO_ROOT] [--mode MODE]
                        [--dry-run-enumerate]
                        [--filter-local-ids FILTER_LOCAL_IDS]

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --repo-root REPO_ROOT
                        Repository root (default: auto-detect from script
                        location)
  --mode MODE           Rollout-safety mode: reconcile-check | dry-run |
                        bootstrap-strict | bootstrap-throttle | live (default:
                        live)
  --dry-run-enumerate   Print the list of ticket-tracker entries that the
                        reconciler would enumerate (after .scratch/ exclusion)
                        and exit without running a pass. Each entry is printed
                        as an absolute path, one per line.
  --filter-local-ids FILTER_LOCAL_IDS
                        Comma-separated list of local ticket IDs. When set,
                        all three differs run on their full unfiltered inputs
                        (same code paths as production) but only mutations
                        targeting these IDs (or their bound Jira keys) reach
                        the applier. For validation use only.
